    "We then identified differentially methylated probes (DMP) among all groups at different developmental stages and found that DMP numbers were significantly different, with PT organoids showing the lowest and PTN organoids exhibiting the highest (Fig. 3b).",
    "Interestingly, the methylation level of the mesenchymal subtype was also shown to be the highest among all three GB subtypes (Supplementary Fig. 3a) 26.",
    "The dynamic changes of DNA methylation in the LEGOs over time demonstrate that the DNA methylome is actively changing during tumor progression (Fig. 3b), including both hypomethylated and hypermethylated probes, particularly during the early developmental stage of brain tumors (Fig.",
    "However, it remains unclear what regulates these dynamic DNA methylome changes during tumor development.",
    "We performed a gene set enrichment analysis (GSEA) on the DMPs located on different gene features at various stages."
  ]
